JOHANNESBURG – Spain's national coach Julen Lopetegui will replace Zinedine Zidane as Real Madrid coach after the 2018 World Cup in Russia.
	
	The Spanish giants broke the news in a Tweet on Tuesday. Official Announcement: Julen Lopetegui will be the #RealMadrid coach after the celebration of the 2018 World Cup.https://t.co/QcDiu6UjHV pic.twitter.com/iA1PnUdrtT "Julen Lopetegui will be the Real Madrid coach after the celebration of the 2018 World Cup," the Tweet said. READ: Zidane fuels Neymar to Madrid speculation He is said to have signed a three-year contract with the Los Blancos. "Julen Lopetegui will join the club after Spain’s participation in the World Cup, after two years leading the national team," the club's official website announced. eNCA